sources.title: Female Jungle
sources.description: Title: Female Jungle Summary: Several persons, including an off duty policeman and a weird rich guy, are suspects in the murder of a beautiful actress. Directed by: Bruno VeSota Actors: Lawrence Tierney, Jayne Mansfield, John Carradine Production Company: Bert Kaiser Productions Inc. Release Date: 16 June 1956 (USA) Aspect Ratio: 1.37 : 1 A blonde actress is murdered across from a bar. An off-duty cop has been getting pleasantly sloshed, but becomes worried about his innocence when he finds out he was seen leaving the establishment with a blonde, but doesn't remember. As he investigates, he interviews a columnist who was going with the actress, a caricaturist who drew the victim, the caricaturist's wife who works at the bar, and the caricaturist's lover, and slowly begins to put the pieces of the deadly puzzle together.
